<h2>Gay</h2>
	<p>Gay is a term generally used to describe when a man or man-aligned* person is attracted specifically to another man or man-aligned person, but it is also used as an umbrella term for anyones attraction to the same gender.</p>
<div class="container">
  <img src="file:///C:/Users/Caelyn%20Pettyjohn/Downloads/Queer%20Youth/MLM.png" alt="Mlm" class="image">
  <div class="overlay">
    <div class="text">This flag is the mlm gay flag, but there is also the rainbow which is more widely known.</div>
  </div>
</div>
	
<h2>Lesbian</h2>
	<p>Lesbian is a term for when a woman or woman-aligned* person is attracted to another woman or woman aligned person.</p>
	
<div class="container">
  <img src="file:///C:/Users/Caelyn%20Pettyjohn/Downloads/Queer%20Youth/Lesbean.png" alt="Lesbean" class="image">
  <div class="overlay">
    <div class="text">This flag is the Sunset Lesbian flag, but there are many different versions. Not one is exactly <i>right</i>, so use whichever one you resonate with.</div>
  </div>
</div>
	
<h2>Bi and Pan</h2>
	<p>Bi and pan is the attraction to two or more genders. Within this community, there has been dispute on the difference between the two. I personally do not know the difference, but bisexuality is more categorized as the attraction to both male and female.</p>
	<div class="container">
  <img src="file:///C:/Users/Caelyn%20Pettyjohn/Downloads/Queer%20Youth/Bi.png" alt="Bi" class="image">
