  </div>
</div>
<h3>|->Bicurious, Biromantic, Omnisexual, Panromantic, Polysexual</h3>

<h2>Heterosexual</h2>
	<p>Heterosexual or "straight" is the romantic or sexual attraction to someone of the opposite gender.</p>
<h3>|->Heteromantic</h3>

<h2>Homosexual</h2>
	<p>An outdated term which describes the romantic or sexual attraction to someone of the same gender. It is reccomded not to use this term.</p>
<h3>|-> Homoromantic</h3>

<h2>Queer</h2>
	<p>Often used as a slur historically, Queer is an umbrella term in which any/all LGBTQ+ may identity. It is not reccomended to be used by anyone outside of the community because of its past.</p>

<h2>Aromantic</h2>
	<p>Little to no romantic attraction to anyone of any gender.</p>

<h2>Asexual</h2>
	<p>While being a spectrum, it is generally described as little to no sexual attraction to any gender.</p>
<h3>|->Graysexual, Greyromantic, Demiromantic, Demisexual</h3>

<h2>Gynesexual & Androsexual</h2>
	<p>These two identities are very similar to lesbian and gay, but there is a main difference; with Gynesexual, it is the attraction to anyone who <i>presents femininity</i>.</p>
	
<p>Polyamorous</p>

<h4>*A woman or man aligned person is someone who is not entirely a woman or man, but feels more alined with that label. For example, a nonbinary person can still be a lesbian if they are woman-aligned and feel attraction mainly to women.</h4>

